<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-15T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2073a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Paraguay (<persName type="to">Wheeler</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-15T18:00:00-04:00">August
                                        15, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>32. Please discuss fully and frankly with President <persName corresp="#p_AE3">Ayala</persName> and his Government the Chaco
                                situation and cable fully his views regarding it and any suggestions
                                they may have to make regarding a settlement.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>